\i0 Self help is a paradox that ultimately puts you in the hands of your imperfect fallible self. Self help is dependent on self-diagnosing your own problems and labeling them some version of a deficiency then going in and fixing yourself. It tells you there's a better version of you, and makes vague comparisons between what you could be and how you could do it to be "it".\
\
organize your self as you would a workspace. self-systemize and regulate into a state of homeostasis and balance. the fine-tuning can be supplemented by outside-aid. \
\
Thankfully, you are not the problem (at least not entirely). The space and objects that surround you encourage certain elements of your behavior, giving you easy access to decisions that no good. \
\
With this degree project I'm proposing a new kind of self help. It's an object / space-based help. The guide comes from the outside in, though restructuring your life through your environment. First step is optimizing your space. This idealized space keeps everything contained and everything relevant relevant. Nothing is lost in deep storage, misplaced and forgotten, nor are the things left too active, live stimulus buzzing and distracting. A person is mobile, so why should his/her space be stagnant? Or even worse, why should it be bigger/stronger/more permanent than our agency? The The ultimate goal is for the user to be comfortably in control. For the space to be made to a human-scaled living, more specifically, to the user. Of course, this idealized space cannot happen without input from the user. The whole creation of this space is through a constant feedback loop between the user and his/her space. Within the space, its objects are mobile and customizable, the pieces seizing the immediate close relative to me taking ownership of my space The system integrates within a life, my life. It's part of the physical toolkit to free you from whatever hangups you have with making rough with the things you own. On a bigger level, it's advocating you to truly know your objects and spaces, taking it beyond the layers of seemingly magical fabrication manufacturing methods and reclaiming the agency to do. \
\
Currently the piece feels a little dressed up with the spray paint - playing safe within the wishy-washy qualifiers of a finished piece. Also the grid is obviously artificial but when inside a real room will be better integrated. The color masking is supposed to flatten the piece and reduce it to its bare relationships without too much noise. The DIY is not pushed far enough. To go forward in the future I want to push the jankiness / MacGyver /DIY spirit. I want to readjust my thinking, move it away from catering to many and any format of a surface good and just keep it quality in the sense that it is compatible to my life. Compatibility for me means having the ability to move and adjust to my body and staying aligned comfortably to those patterns of behaviors. I want to secure it with tabs and rivets that speak to no sense of hinge things off of one another by way of Irwin Quickgrips making planes and surfaces and hotspots gathering energy. staying close to the lip of a cliff so that the fall into kinetic energy will come easier. leaving the inertia with a jumpstart. \

