\i0 The implications of this work lies in creating a mental state of mind that would encourage a healthy lifestyle. The pieces were ultimately a part of an instructional toolkit that would enable people like myself to take ownership of my space and overcome my inability to react to the world around me. Just telling people to "deal with it" is not a method of effective repair. We are creatures of comfort, only when we are pushed do we begin to make change. We shape our bodies to the crevices that will fit us only when we know it's our own or when we have no other choice. Now it's possible to be in charge of that environment and indeed help yourself. \
